<subSubSection id="C311AFCBFF94BD42FF2EFBDE8A63FBF4" pageId="3" pageNumber="1552" type="etymology">
<paragraph id="8BB4FC40FF94BD42FF2EFBDE8A63FBF4" blockId="3.[178,1086,1070,1121]" pageId="3" pageNumber="1552">Etymology: The name (Latin, adjective: skinny) refers to the slender habitus, one of the characters distinguishing this species from similar congeners.</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection id="C311AFCBFF94BD45FF2EFB808893F994" lastPageId="4" lastPageNumber="1553" pageId="3" pageNumber="1552" type="description">
<paragraph id="8BB4FC40FF94BD42FF2EFB808BF2FB54" blockId="3.[178,1086,1136,1217]" pageId="3" pageNumber="1552">
Description: Small and slender species, 
<quantity id="4CF351A5FF94BD42FD23FB808A16FB13" box="[703,788,1136,1158]" metricMagnitude="-3" metricUnit="m" metricValue="2.7" pageId="3" pageNumber="1552" unit="mm" value="2.7">2.7 mm</quantity>
. Coloration: Head blackish; pronotum blackish-brown; elytra dark-brown; abdomen blackish, with the apex (segments VII-X) dark-brown. Legs and antennae yellowish.
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="8BB4FC40FF94BD42FF2EFB208A29FAAB" blockId="3.[178,1086,1232,1342]" pageId="3" pageNumber="1552">
Head moderately transverse, approximately 1.15 times as broad as long; punctation conspicuously coarse and dense, only slightly sparser in posterior portion of dorsal surface (
<figureCitation id="1330E0C5FF94BD42FF26FAFB89F4FAB4" box="[186,246,1291,1313]" captionStart="Figs 1-8" captionStartId="4.[178,218,1229,1249]" captionTargetBox="[179,1085,212,1212]" captionTargetId="figure-201@4.[178,1085,212,1218]" captionTargetPageId="4" captionText="Figs 1-8: Neosclerus macer nov.sp. (1-7) and N. schuelkei ASSING (8): (1) forebody; (2) male sternite VII; (3) male sternite VIII in ventral view; (4) anterior carinae of male sternite VIII in ventral view; (5) male sternite VIII in lateral view; (6, 8) aedeagus in lateral view; (7) apical portion of aedeagus in ventral view. Scale bars: 1: 0.5 mm; 2-3, 5: 0.2 mm; 4, 6-8: 0.1 mm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5302506" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/5302506/files/figure.png" pageId="3" pageNumber="1552">Fig. 1</figureCitation>
); interstices without microsculpture and glossy. Eyes large, but not reaching posterior margin of head; postocular portion short, but noticeable.
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="8BB4FC40FF94BD42FF2EFABE8B57FA0B" blockId="3.[178,1086,1357,1438]" pageId="3" pageNumber="1552">
Pronotum approximately as long as broad and 0.85 times as wide as head; punctation as coarse and almost as dense as that of head (
<figureCitation id="1330E0C5FF94BD42FDE5FA9B8BB5FA14" box="[633,695,1387,1409]" captionStart="Figs 1-8" captionStartId="4.[178,218,1229,1249]" captionTargetBox="[179,1085,212,1212]" captionTargetId="figure-201@4.[178,1085,212,1218]" captionTargetPageId="4" captionText="Figs 1-8: Neosclerus macer nov.sp. (1-7) and N. schuelkei ASSING (8): (1) forebody; (2) male sternite VII; (3) male sternite VIII in ventral view; (4) anterior carinae of male sternite VIII in ventral view; (5) male sternite VIII in lateral view; (6, 8) aedeagus in lateral view; (7) apical portion of aedeagus in ventral view. Scale bars: 1: 0.5 mm; 2-3, 5: 0.2 mm; 4, 6-8: 0.1 mm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5302506" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/5302506/files/figure.png" pageId="3" pageNumber="1552">Fig. 1</figureCitation>
); midline narrowly impunctate; interstices without microsculpture and glossy.
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="8BB4FC40FF94BD42FF2EFA5D89D0F98E" blockId="3.[178,1086,1453,1563]" pageId="3" pageNumber="1552">
Elytra approximately as long as pronotum (
<figureCitation id="1330E0C5FF94BD42FDEAFA5D8BB1FA56" box="[630,691,1453,1475]" captionStart="Figs 1-8" captionStartId="4.[178,218,1229,1249]" captionTargetBox="[179,1085,212,1212]" captionTargetId="figure-201@4.[178,1085,212,1218]" captionTargetPageId="4" captionText="Figs 1-8: Neosclerus macer nov.sp. (1-7) and N. schuelkei ASSING (8): (1) forebody; (2) male sternite VII; (3) male sternite VIII in ventral view; (4) anterior carinae of male sternite VIII in ventral view; (5) male sternite VIII in lateral view; (6, 8) aedeagus in lateral view; (7) apical portion of aedeagus in ventral view. Scale bars: 1: 0.5 mm; 2-3, 5: 0.2 mm; 4, 6-8: 0.1 mm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5302506" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/5302506/files/figure.png" pageId="3" pageNumber="1552">Fig. 1</figureCitation>
); punctation dense, defined, and relatively coarse, but distinctly less so than that of head and pronotum. Hind wings fully developed. Metatarsomere I longer than II, but shorter than the combined length of II and III.
</paragraph>
<caption id="DF74ACC8FF93BD45FF2EFB3D8AD0FAB0" ID-DOI="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5302506" ID-Zenodo-Dep="5302506" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/5302506/files/figure.png" pageId="4" pageNumber="1553" startId="4.[178,218,1229,1249]" targetBox="[179,1085,212,1212]" targetPageId="4">
<paragraph id="8BB4FC40FF93BD45FF2EFB3D8AD0FAB0" blockId="4.[178,1086,1229,1317]" pageId="4" pageNumber="1553">
<emphasis id="B97F2052FF93BD45FF2EFB3D8801FB74" bold="true" box="[178,259,1229,1249]" pageId="4" pageNumber="1553">Figs 1-8</emphasis>
: 
<taxonomicName id="4C0B87C3FF93BD45FE8EFB3D88BBFB74" authority="Assing, 2013" authorityName="Assing" authorityYear="2013" box="[274,441,1229,1249]" class="Insecta" family="Staphylinidae" genus="Neosclerus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="4" pageNumber="1553" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="macer" status="nov.sp.">
<emphasis id="B97F2052FF93BD45FE8EFB3D88BBFB74" box="[274,441,1229,1249]" italics="true" pageId="4" pageNumber="1553">Neosclerus macer</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
<taxonomicNameLabel id="A24C9D29FF93BD45FE5FFB3D8B04FB74" box="[451,518,1229,1249]" pageId="4" pageNumber="1553" rank="species">nov.sp.</taxonomicNameLabel>
(
<emphasis id="B97F2052FF93BD45FD8AFB3D8B36FB74" bold="true" box="[534,564,1229,1249]" pageId="4" pageNumber="1553">1-7</emphasis>
) and 
<taxonomicName id="4C0B87C3FF93BD45FDECFB3D8A31FB75" authority="ASSING" authorityName="ASSING" box="[624,819,1229,1249]" class="Insecta" family="Staphylinidae" genus="Neosclerus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="4" pageNumber="1553" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="schuelkei">
<emphasis id="B97F2052FF93BD45FDECFB3D8BE1FB74" box="[624,739,1229,1249]" italics="true" pageId="4" pageNumber="1553">N. schuelkei</emphasis>
ASSING
</taxonomicName>
(
<emphasis id="B97F2052FF93BD45FCD8FB3D8A4DFB74" bold="true" box="[836,847,1229,1249]" pageId="4" pageNumber="1553">8</emphasis>
): (
<emphasis id="B97F2052FF93BD45FCF2FB3D8A7BFB74" bold="true" box="[878,889,1229,1249]" pageId="4" pageNumber="1553">1</emphasis>
) forebody; (
<emphasis id="B97F2052FF93BD45FC69FB3D8D02FB74" bold="true" box="[1013,1024,1229,1249]" pageId="4" pageNumber="1553">2</emphasis>
) male sternite VII; (
<emphasis id="B97F2052FF93BD45FEA8FB14883DFB6D" bold="true" box="[308,319,1252,1272]" pageId="4" pageNumber="1553">3</emphasis>
) male sternite VIII in ventral view; (
<emphasis id="B97F2052FF93BD45FD3BFB148BB0FB6D" bold="true" box="[679,690,1252,1272]" pageId="4" pageNumber="1553">4</emphasis>
) anterior carinae of male sternite VIII in ventral view; (
<emphasis id="B97F2052FF93BD45FEA5FB0B8846FA9A" bold="true" box="[313,324,1275,1295]" pageId="4" pageNumber="1553">5</emphasis>
) male sternite VIII in lateral view; (
<emphasis id="B97F2052FF93BD45FD04FB0B8BBEFA9A" bold="true" box="[664,700,1275,1295]" pageId="4" pageNumber="1553">6, 8</emphasis>
) aedeagus in lateral view; (
<emphasis id="B97F2052FF93BD45FC5CFB0B8AC9FA9A" bold="true" box="[960,971,1275,1295]" pageId="4" pageNumber="1553">7</emphasis>
) apical portion of aedeagus in ventral view. Scale bars: 1: 0.5 mm; 2-3, 5: 0.2 mm; 4, 6-8: 0.1 mm.
</paragraph>
</caption>
<paragraph id="8BB4FC40FF93BD45FF2EFAC489F4FAF2" blockId="4.[178,1085,1332,1383]" pageId="4" pageNumber="1553">Abdomen distinctly narrower than elytra; posterior margin of tergite VII with palisade fringe.</paragraph>
<paragraph id="8BB4FC40FF93BD45FF5BFA878893F994" blockId="4.[178,1086,1398,1537]" pageId="4" pageNumber="1553">
: sternite VII weakly oblong and with sparse pubescence, posterior margin with pair of small tooth-like processes (
<figureCitation id="1330E0C5FF93BD45FE53FA648B12FA3F" box="[463,528,1428,1450]" captionStart="Figs 1-8" captionStartId="4.[178,218,1229,1249]" captionTargetBox="[179,1085,212,1212]" captionTargetId="figure-201@4.[178,1085,212,1218]" captionTargetPageId="4" captionText="Figs 1-8: Neosclerus macer nov.sp. (1-7) and N. schuelkei ASSING (8): (1) forebody; (2) male sternite VII; (3) male sternite VIII in ventral view; (4) anterior carinae of male sternite VIII in ventral view; (5) male sternite VIII in lateral view; (6, 8) aedeagus in lateral view; (7) apical portion of aedeagus in ventral view. Scale bars: 1: 0.5 mm; 2-3, 5: 0.2 mm; 4, 6-8: 0.1 mm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5302506" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/5302506/files/figure.png" pageId="4" pageNumber="1553">Fig. 2</figureCitation>
); sternite VIII oblong, anteriorly with pair of carinae posteriorly extending into a short process with a terminal seta, posterior excision moderately deep (
<figureCitation id="1330E0C5FF93BD45FEB5FA3E8880FA71" box="[297,386,1486,1508]" captionStart="Figs 1-8" captionStartId="4.[178,218,1229,1249]" captionTargetBox="[179,1085,212,1212]" captionTargetId="figure-201@4.[178,1085,212,1218]" captionTargetPageId="4" captionText="Figs 1-8: Neosclerus macer nov.sp. (1-7) and N. schuelkei ASSING (8): (1) forebody; (2) male sternite VII; (3) male sternite VIII in ventral view; (4) anterior carinae of male sternite VIII in ventral view; (5) male sternite VIII in lateral view; (6, 8) aedeagus in lateral view; (7) apical portion of aedeagus in ventral view. Scale bars: 1: 0.5 mm; 2-3, 5: 0.2 mm; 4, 6-8: 0.1 mm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5302506" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/5302506/files/figure.png" pageId="4" pageNumber="1553">Figs 3-5</figureCitation>
); aedeagus 
<quantity id="4CF351A5FF93BD45FE60FA3E8B55FA71" box="[508,599,1486,1508]" metricMagnitude="-4" metricUnit="m" metricValue="4.5" pageId="4" pageNumber="1553" unit="mm" value="0.45">0.45 mm</quantity>
long, ventral process subapically bent and apically acute (
<figureCitation id="1330E0C5FF93BD45FEB1FA1B8886F994" box="[301,388,1515,1537]" captionStart="Figs 1-8" captionStartId="4.[178,218,1229,1249]" captionTargetBox="[179,1085,212,1212]" captionTargetId="figure-201@4.[178,1085,212,1218]" captionTargetPageId="4" captionText="Figs 1-8: Neosclerus macer nov.sp. (1-7) and N. schuelkei ASSING (8): (1) forebody; (2) male sternite VII; (3) male sternite VIII in ventral view; (4) anterior carinae of male sternite VIII in ventral view; (5) male sternite VIII in lateral view; (6, 8) aedeagus in lateral view; (7) apical portion of aedeagus in ventral view. Scale bars: 1: 0.5 mm; 2-3, 5: 0.2 mm; 4, 6-8: 0.1 mm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5302506" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/5302506/files/figure.png" pageId="4" pageNumber="1553">Figs 6-7</figureCitation>
).
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection id="C311AFCBFF93BD44FF2EF9E18A9EFD80" lastPageId="5" lastPageNumber="1554" pageId="4" pageNumber="1553" type="discussion">
<paragraph id="8BB4FC40FF93BD44FF2EF9E18A9EFD80" blockId="4.[178,1086,1553,1604]" lastBlockId="5.[178,1086,218,533]" lastPageId="5" lastPageNumber="1554" pageId="4" pageNumber="1553">
Comparative notes: Based on the synapomorphically derived shapes of the male sternites VII (bidentate posterior margin) and VIII (anteriorly bicarinate), as well as on the similar general morphology of the aedeagus, 
<taxonomicName id="4C0B87C3FF92BD44FD6FFF2B8A54FF65" authorityName="Assing" authorityYear="2013" box="[755,854,219,240]" class="Insecta" family="Staphylinidae" genus="Neosclerus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="5" pageNumber="1554" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="macer">
<emphasis id="B97F2052FF92BD44FD6FFF2B8A54FF65" box="[755,854,219,240]" italics="true" pageId="5" pageNumber="1554">N. macer</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
is undoubtedly most closely related to 
<taxonomicName id="4C0B87C3FF92BD44FEF0FF098B92FE9B" authority="ASSING 2011" authorityName="ASSING" authorityYear="2011" box="[364,656,248,270]" class="Insecta" family="Staphylinidae" genus="Neosclerus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="5" pageNumber="1554" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="bicarinatus">
<emphasis id="B97F2052FF92BD44FEF0FF0988FDFE9B" box="[364,511,248,270]" italics="true" pageId="5" pageNumber="1554">N. bicarinatus</emphasis>
<bibRefCitation id="EF9A81B1FF92BD44FD94FF088B92FE9B" author="ASSING V" box="[520,656,248,270]" journalOrPublisher="Beitrage zur Entomologie, Keltern" pageId="5" pageNumber="1554" pagination="89 - 148" part="61" refId="ref3466" refString="ASSING V. (2011 a): A revision of the genus Neosclerus CAMERON (Coleoptera: Staphylinidae: Paederinae). - Beitrage zur Entomologie, Keltern 61 (1): 89 - 148." title="A revision of the genus Neosclerus CAMERON (Coleoptera: Staphylinidae: Paederinae)" type="journal article" year="2011">ASSING 2011</bibRefCitation>
</taxonomicName>
from 
<collectingCountry id="F31CBCD0FF92BD44FD4EFF088A29FE9B" box="[722,811,248,270]" name="Vietnam" pageId="5" pageNumber="1554">Vietnam</collectingCountry>
, most likely its sister species. In the key in 
<bibRefCitation id="EF9A81B1FF92BD44FEF1FEE58B12FEBE" author="ASSING V" box="[365,528,277,299]" journalOrPublisher="Beitrage zur Entomologie, Keltern" pageId="5" pageNumber="1554" pagination="89 - 148" part="61" refId="ref3466" refString="ASSING V. (2011 a): A revision of the genus Neosclerus CAMERON (Coleoptera: Staphylinidae: Paederinae). - Beitrage zur Entomologie, Keltern 61 (1): 89 - 148." title="A revision of the genus Neosclerus CAMERON (Coleoptera: Staphylinidae: Paederinae)" type="journal article" year="2011">ASSING (2011a)</bibRefCitation>
, the new species would key out at couplet 16, together with 
<taxonomicName id="4C0B87C3FF92BD44FF76FEC388E3FEDD" authority="ASSING 2011" authorityName="ASSING" authorityYear="2011" box="[234,481,306,328]" class="Insecta" family="Staphylinidae" genus="Neosclerus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="5" pageNumber="1554" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="glaber">
<emphasis id="B97F2052FF92BD44FF76FEC3884FFEDD" box="[234,333,306,328]" italics="true" pageId="5" pageNumber="1554">N. glaber</emphasis>
<bibRefCitation id="EF9A81B1FF92BD44FEC4FEC288E3FEDD" author="ASSING V" box="[344,481,306,328]" journalOrPublisher="Beitrage zur Entomologie, Keltern" pageId="5" pageNumber="1554" pagination="89 - 148" part="61" refId="ref3466" refString="ASSING V. (2011 a): A revision of the genus Neosclerus CAMERON (Coleoptera: Staphylinidae: Paederinae). - Beitrage zur Entomologie, Keltern 61 (1): 89 - 148." title="A revision of the genus Neosclerus CAMERON (Coleoptera: Staphylinidae: Paederinae)" type="journal article" year="2011">ASSING 2011</bibRefCitation>
</taxonomicName>
and 
<taxonomicName id="4C0B87C3FF92BD44FD87FEC38BADFEDD" authorityName="ASSING" authorityYear="2011" box="[539,687,306,328]" class="Insecta" family="Staphylinidae" genus="Neosclerus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="5" pageNumber="1554" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="bicarinatus">
<emphasis id="B97F2052FF92BD44FD87FEC38BADFEDD" box="[539,687,306,328]" italics="true" pageId="5" pageNumber="1554">N. bicarinatus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
. It is distinguished from both by the shape of the aedeagus, the more slender pronotum, and the distinctly coarser punctation of the elytra, from 
<taxonomicName id="4C0B87C3FF92BD44FEE4FE9E88D8FE16" authorityName="ASSING" authorityYear="2011" box="[376,474,365,387]" class="Insecta" family="Staphylinidae" genus="Neosclerus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="5" pageNumber="1554" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="glaber">
<emphasis id="B97F2052FF92BD44FEE4FE9E88D8FE16" box="[376,474,365,387]" italics="true" pageId="5" pageNumber="1554">N. glaber</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
additionally by the modifications of the male sternites VII and VIII, and from 
<taxonomicName id="4C0B87C3FF92BD44FEE2FE7B8B12FE35" authorityName="ASSING" authorityYear="2011" box="[382,528,394,416]" class="Insecta" family="Staphylinidae" genus="Neosclerus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="5" pageNumber="1554" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="bicarinatus">
<emphasis id="B97F2052FF92BD44FEE2FE7B8B12FE35" box="[382,528,394,416]" italics="true" pageId="5" pageNumber="1554">N. bicarinatus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
by the coarser and denser punctation of the head, the uniformly dark coloration of the elytra (
<taxonomicName id="4C0B87C3FF92BD44FDFFFE588BFAFE28" authorityName="ASSING" authorityYear="2011" box="[611,760,423,445]" class="Insecta" family="Staphylinidae" genus="Neosclerus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="5" pageNumber="1554" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="bicarinatus">
<emphasis id="B97F2052FF92BD44FDFFFE588BFAFE28" box="[611,760,423,445]" italics="true" pageId="5" pageNumber="1554">N. bicarinatus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
: humeral angles and posterior margin reddish), the more narrowly separated and differently shaped carinae on the male sternite VIII, as well as by the less pronounced posterior processes of the male sternite VII. For illustrations of 
<taxonomicName id="4C0B87C3FF92BD44FE39FDF08B06FD80" authorityName="ASSING" authorityYear="2011" box="[421,516,511,533]" class="Insecta" family="Staphylinidae" genus="Neosclerus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="5" pageNumber="1554" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="glaber">
<emphasis id="B97F2052FF92BD44FE39FDF08B06FD80" box="[421,516,511,533]" italics="true" pageId="5" pageNumber="1554">N. glaber</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
and 
<taxonomicName id="4C0B87C3FF92BD44FDAAFDF08BC4FD80" authorityName="ASSING" authorityYear="2011" box="[566,710,511,533]" class="Insecta" family="Staphylinidae" genus="Neosclerus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="5" pageNumber="1554" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="bicarinatus">
<emphasis id="B97F2052FF92BD44FDAAFDF08BC4FD80" box="[566,710,511,533]" italics="true" pageId="5" pageNumber="1554">N. bicarinatus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
see 
<bibRefCitation id="EF9A81B1FF92BD44FD6FFE0F8A9AFD80" author="ASSING V" box="[755,920,511,533]" journalOrPublisher="Beitrage zur Entomologie, Keltern" pageId="5" pageNumber="1554" pagination="89 - 148" part="61" refId="ref3466" refString="ASSING V. (2011 a): A revision of the genus Neosclerus CAMERON (Coleoptera: Staphylinidae: Paederinae). - Beitrage zur Entomologie, Keltern 61 (1): 89 - 148." title="A revision of the genus Neosclerus CAMERON (Coleoptera: Staphylinidae: Paederinae)" type="journal article" year="2011">ASSING (2011a)</bibRefCitation>
.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection id="C311AFCBFF92BD44FF2EFDD48BD6FDE0" pageId="5" pageNumber="1554" type="distribution">
<paragraph id="8BB4FC40FF92BD44FF2EFDD48BD6FDE0" blockId="5.[178,1085,548,629]" pageId="5" pageNumber="1554">
Distribution and bionomics: ThetypelocalityissituatedinPhongsaly province in northern 
<collectingCountry id="F31CBCD0FF92BD44FE5EFDB388F1FDCD" box="[450,499,579,600]" name="Laos" pageId="5" pageNumber="1554">Laos</collectingCountry>
(
<figureCitation id="1330E0C5FF92BD44FD9FFDB28B4AFDCD" box="[515,584,578,600]" captionStart="Map 1" captionStartId="1.[178,223,1480,1500]" captionTargetBox="[178,1085,714,1470]" captionTargetId="figure-204@1.[178,1085,714,1470]" captionTargetPageId="1" captionText="Map 1: Distributions of Neosclerus macer nov.sp. (open circle) and N. barbatulus ASSING (filled and open circles) in South Asia." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5302502" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/5302502/files/figure.png" pageId="5" pageNumber="1554">Map 1</figureCitation>
) at an altitude of 
<quantity id="4CF351A5FF92BD44FC90FDB28A5CFDCD" box="[780,862,578,600]" metricMagnitude="3" metricUnit="m" metricValue="1.5" pageId="5" pageNumber="1554" unit="m" value="1500.0">1500 m</quantity>
. The fully developed hind wings suggest that 
<taxonomicName id="4C0B87C3FF92BD44FE3AFD908B01FDE0" authorityName="Assing" authorityYear="2013" box="[422,515,608,629]" class="Insecta" family="Staphylinidae" genus="Neosclerus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="5" pageNumber="1554" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="macer">
<emphasis id="B97F2052FF92BD44FE3AFD908B01FDE0" box="[422,515,608,629]" italics="true" pageId="5" pageNumber="1554">N. macer</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
may be widespread.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
